tissueExpression.summary: Exocrine pancreas, thyroid, decidual cells, epididymis, a subset of cells in lymphoid tissues and bone marrow showed strong cytoplasmic staining. Spleen, myocytes, glial cells, breast and alveolar cells were mainly negative. Remaining normal tissues showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic and occasional membranous positivity.

A majority of cancer tissues showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity. A few cases of ovarian and colorectal cancers exhibited strong staining. Lymphomas, breast, urothelial and renal cancers were in general negative.

tissueExpression.summary: Most normal tissues showed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity in granular pattern. Pneumocytes, glomeruli of kidney, glial cells of CNS, spleen, ovarian and endometrial stromal cells were negative.

A majority of cancer tissues displayed weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Distinct membranous positivity was seen in colorectal cancers. Occasional cases of melanomas and thyroid cancers exhibited strong immunoreactivity. Several cases of lymphomas, gliomas, cervical, ovarian and skin cancers were negative.
